---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CTA from '../../components/CTA.astro';
import FAQ from '../../components/FAQ.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'How often should I have my AC serviced in Arizona?',
    a: 'In Arizona, we recommend a professional tune-up at least once per year — ideally in early spring before the cooling season begins. Because our systems run so hard and so long (often 9–10 months per year), some homeowners and commercial properties opt for a spring and fall inspection. Annual maintenance significantly extends equipment life and reduces unexpected breakdowns.'
  },
  {
    q: 'What is included in an AC tune-up from Altered Air?',
    a: 'Our seasonal tune-up includes: thermostat calibration check, air filter inspection and replacement, condenser and evaporator coil cleaning, refrigerant level check, electrical connections inspection, capacitor and contactor testing, blower motor and belt inspection, condensate drain flushing, and a full system performance test. We document findings and give you a written report.'
  },
  {
    q: 'Can maintenance prevent a mid-summer AC breakdown?',
    a: 'Yes — significantly. Most AC failures during summer are caused by issues that a trained technician can identify months in advance: a capacitor on its way out, refrigerant slowly leaking, a dirty condenser coil causing overheating. Finding these problems in March is a minor repair. Discovering them in July at 115°F is an emergency. Maintenance pays for itself many times over.'
  },
  {
    q: 'Do you offer maintenance plans or service agreements?',
    a: 'Yes. Ask us about our maintenance agreements when you call <a href="tel:+17605941125">(760) 594-1125</a>. A maintenance plan gives you priority scheduling, discounted repair rates, and the peace of mind that your system is professionally serviced before each season.'
  },
  {
    q: 'How does duct sealing improve AC performance?',
    a: 'In a typical West Valley home, 20–30% of conditioned air is lost through leaky ductwork — meaning your AC is running harder than necessary to maintain comfort. Properly sealing ducts improves airflow, reduces energy bills, and takes significant strain off your equipment. We evaluate duct condition as part of our comprehensive tune-up.'
  }
];
---

<Layout
  title="AC Maintenance in Buckeye, AZ | Altered Air | (760) 594-1125"
  description="Seasonal AC tune-ups and maintenance in Buckeye, AZ. Coil cleaning, filter replacement, efficiency testing, and duct sealing to prevent summer breakdowns. Call (760) 594-1125."
  canonical="/services/ac-maintenance"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> → Services → AC Maintenance</p>
      <h1>AC Maintenance &amp; Tune-Ups — Buckeye, AZ</h1>
      <p>
        In Arizona's brutal summers, a well-maintained AC system is the difference between a comfortable home
        and an emergency call at midnight. Altered Air provides professional AC maintenance throughout
        Buckeye and the West Valley — catching small problems before they become expensive failures.
      </p>
      <a href="tel:+17605941125" class="phone-link">&#128222; Schedule Maintenance: (760) 594-1125</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-two-col">
        <div>
          <h2>Why AC Maintenance Matters in Arizona</h2>
          <p>
            West Valley AC systems work harder than almost anywhere in the country. In Buckeye, your air
            conditioner may run 10 or more months per year, and on peak summer days it cycles nearly
            continuously to maintain indoor comfort against 115°F outdoor temperatures.
          </p>
          <p>
            That kind of workload accelerates wear on every component: capacitors, contactors, compressors,
            coils, and fan motors. Without regular maintenance, the cumulative stress leads to failure —
            usually at the worst possible moment.
          </p>
          <p>
            Proper maintenance extends equipment life by 3–5 years on average, reduces energy consumption
            by 5–15%, and dramatically reduces the risk of a summer emergency breakdown. For commercial
            properties, it also means better air quality and compliance with any applicable maintenance
            requirements.
          </p>

          <h2 style="margin-top:2rem;">What We Include in Every AC Tune-Up</h2>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Thermostat calibration and programming review</li>
            <li>Air filter inspection and replacement (filter provided)</li>
            <li>Condenser coil cleaning — removes dust and debris that cause overheating</li>
            <li>Evaporator coil inspection and cleaning</li>
            <li>Refrigerant level check — identify slow leaks before they cause failure</li>
            <li>Electrical connection inspection and tightening</li>
            <li>Capacitor and contactor testing</li>
            <li>Blower motor and belt inspection</li>
            <li>Condensate drain flush and treatment</li>
            <li>System performance test — verify temperature differential</li>
            <li>Written report of all findings and recommendations</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="highlight-box">
            <h3>Spring Maintenance = Summer Peace of Mind</h3>
            <p>
              Schedule your tune-up before the summer rush. April and early May appointments go fast —
              call now to get on the calendar.
            </p>
            <a href="tel:+17605941125" class="phone">(760) 594-1125</a>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Schedule Service</a>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
            <h3>Maintenance Agreements Available</h3>
            <p>
              Altered Air offers maintenance agreements for residential and commercial customers.
              Agreement members receive priority scheduling, annual tune-ups, and discounted
              rates on any repairs needed. Ask about plans when you call.
            </p>
            <a href="tel:+17605941125" class="card-link">Call for Details →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-gray">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Additional Maintenance Services</h2>
      <div class="service-list">
        <div class="service-item">
          <h3>Duct Sealing</h3>
          <p>Leaky ductwork loses 20–30% of conditioned air in a typical Arizona home. We locate and seal duct leaks to improve airflow and reduce energy bills.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-item">
          <h3>Efficiency Testing</h3>
          <p>We measure system efficiency and compare it to manufacturer specs. If your system is underperforming, we identify why and recommend targeted repairs or upgrades.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-item">
          <h3>Coil Deep Cleaning</h3>
          <p>Condenser coils packed with dust and debris can reduce cooling capacity by 30% or more. Our coil cleaning process restores full efficiency and prevents compressor overheating.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-item">
          <h3>Smart Thermostat Setup</h3>
          <p>A properly programmed smart thermostat reduces wear and energy cost. We install and configure smart thermostats as part of a maintenance visit or standalone service.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-item">
          <h3>Indoor Air Quality Check</h3>
          <p>We evaluate filtration effectiveness, identify sources of poor air quality, and recommend appropriate filtration upgrades for homes with allergy or dust concerns.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-item">
          <h3>Commercial Refrigeration Maintenance</h3>
          <p>Separate from AC, we offer comprehensive commercial refrigeration maintenance for walk-in coolers, freezers, and other commercial refrigeration equipment. <a href="/services/refrigeration-maintenance">Learn more →</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Serving the Entire West Valley</h2>
      <p style="max-width:680px; color:var(--gray-600); margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        We provide AC maintenance throughout Buckeye and all surrounding West Valley communities.
        Schedule your spring tune-up before temperatures start climbing.
      </p>
      <div class="location-grid">
        <div class="location-tag"><a href="/locations/buckeye-az">Buckeye</a></div>
        <div class="location-tag"><a href="/locations/goodyear-az">Goodyear</a></div>
        <div class="location-tag"><a href="/locations/queen-creek-az">Queen Creek</a></div>
        <div class="location-tag"><a href="/locations/surprise-az">Surprise</a></div>
        <div class="location-tag"><a href="/locations/avondale-az">Avondale</a></div>
        <div class="location-tag"><a href="/locations/litchfield-park-az">Litchfield Park</a></div>
        <div class="location-tag"><a href="/locations/tolleson-az">Tolleson</a></div>
        <div class="location-tag"><a href="/locations/laveen-az">Laveen</a></div>
        <div class="location-tag"><a href="/locations/peoria-az">Peoria</a></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA
    heading="Schedule Your AC Tune-Up Before Summer Hits"
    subtext="Don't wait until your system fails in July. Call John Rigo at Altered Air for professional AC maintenance throughout Buckeye and the West Valley."
  />

  <FAQ faqs={faqs} heading="AC Maintenance FAQs — Arizona" />
</Layout>
